    "body": {
      "type": "incident_body",
      "details": "CPU utilisation exceeded 95% on 3/5 nodes in the `payment-api` cluster.\n\n## Current state\n\n```\nnode-1: 98.2%  (threshold: 90%)\nnode-2: 96.7%  (threshold: 90%)\nnode-3: 95.1%  (threshold: 90%)\nnode-4: 42.3%  (ok)\nnode-5: 38.1%  (ok)\n```\n\n## Runbook\n\n1. Check [Datadog dashboard](https://app.datadoghq.com/dashboard/abc-123) for traffic patterns\n2. Verify autoscaler status:\n```bash\nkubectl get hpa payment-api -n prod\nkubectl top pods -n prod -l app=payment-api\n```\n3. If autoscaler is stuck, manually scale:\n```bash\nkubectl scale deployment payment-api -n prod --replicas=8\n```\n4. Check partner API rate limits in [Grafana](https://grafana.internal/d/partner-api)\n\n## Escalation\n\n- **L1**: On-call engineer - investigate and scale if needed\n- **L2**: Platform team (#platform-oncall) - if autoscaler is broken\n- **L3**: Partner integrations team - if traffic is from partner API\n\n## Related\n\n- JIRA-4521: Memory leak in v2.14.3\n- [Post-mortem: 2026-02-15 CPU incident](https://wiki.internal/postmortems/2026-02-15)"
    },
