    "body": {
      "type": "incident_body",
      "details": "Disk usage at **94%** on pipeline worker nodes. Approaching critical threshold.\n\n## Affected hosts\n\n| Host | Usage | Mount | Free |\n|------|-------|-------|------|\n| pipeline-worker-3 | 94% | /data | 30 GB |\n| pipeline-worker-5 | 88% | /data | 60 GB |\n\n## Runbook\n\n1. Identify large files:\n```bash\nssh pipeline-worker-3\ndu -sh /data/* | sort -rh | head -20\n```\n2. Check if old Spark checkpoints can be purged:\n```bash\nfind /data/checkpoints -mtime +7 -type f | wc -l\n# If safe, purge:\nfind /data/checkpoints -mtime +7 -type f -delete\n```\n3. Check [disk usage dashboard](https://grafana.internal/d/disk-pipeline)\n4. If recurring, request volume resize via [Terraform PR](https://github.com/acme/infra/blob/main/modules/pipeline/variables.tf)\n\n## Escalation\n\n- **L1**: On-call - clean up old data\n- **L2**: Data platform team (#data-platform) - volume resize"
    },
    "is_mergeable": true,
    "assigned_via": "escalation_policy"
