      "details": "Notification delivery p99 latency exceeded 30s threshold.\n\n## Current metrics\n\n- **p50**: 2.1s (normal)\n- **p95**: 18.4s (elevated)\n- **p99**: 34.2s (breached)\n- **Queue depth**: 12,847 messages\n\n## Runbook\n\n1. Check SQS queue depth and consumer lag:\n```bash\naws sqs get-queue-attributes \\\n  --queue-url https://sqs.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/123456/notifications \\\n  --attribute-names ApproximateNumberOfMessages\n```\n2. Check consumer pod health:\n```bash\nkubectl get pods -n prod -l app=notification-worker\nkubectl logs -n prod -l app=notification-worker --tail=50\n```\n3. Scale consumers if backlogged:\n```bash\nkubectl scale deployment notification-worker -n prod --replicas=10\n```\n\n## Dashboards\n\n- [Notification latency](https://grafana.internal/d/notif-latency)\n- [SQS queue metrics](https://grafana.internal/d/sqs-queues)"
