    "body": {
      "type": "incident_body",
      "details": "Consumer group `events-processor` has stopped consuming from Kafka topic `events`.\n\n## Current state\n\n```\nTopic: events (partitions: 24)\nConsumer group: events-processor\nLag: 1,247,832 messages\nLast commit: 2h47m ago\n```\n\n## Runbook\n\n1. Check consumer group status:\n```bash\nkafka-consumer-groups.sh --bootstrap-server kafka:9092 \\\n  --group events-processor --describe\n```\n2. Check if consumer pods are running:\n```bash\nkubectl get pods -n prod -l app=events-processor\nkubectl logs -n prod -l app=events-processor --tail=100\n```\n3. If pods are stuck in CrashLoopBackOff, check for poison messages:\n```bash\nkafka-console-consumer.sh --bootstrap-server kafka:9092 \\\n  --topic events --partition 0 --offset latest --max-messages 1\n```\n4. To skip bad offset and resume:\n```bash\nkafka-consumer-groups.sh --bootstrap-server kafka:9092 \\\n  --group events-processor --topic events --reset-offsets \\\n  --shift-by 1 --execute\n```\n\n## References\n\n- [Kafka runbook](https://wiki.internal/runbooks/kafka)\n- [Consumer lag dashboard](https://grafana.internal/d/kafka-consumer-lag)"
    },
    "is_mergeable": true,
    "assigned_via": "escalation_policy"
  },
