    "body": {
      "type": "incident_body",
      "details": "Heap usage growing linearly since deploy of v3.2.1.\n\n## Current state\n\n- **Heap**: 3.8 GB / 4 GB limit\n- **Growth rate**: ~200 MB/hour\n- **ETA to OOM**: ~1 hour\n\n## Timeline\n\n| Time  | Event |\n|-------|-------|\n| 14:00 | v3.2.1 deployed |\n| 14:30 | Heap crossed 2 GB |\n| 15:00 | Heap crossed 3 GB |\n| 15:12 | Alert fired |\n\n## Suspected cause\n\nNew `UserSessionCache` introduced in v3.2.1 does not evict expired entries.\n\n```go\n// user_session_cache.go:42 - missing TTL eviction\nfunc (c *UserSessionCache) Get(key string) (*Session, bool) {\n    c.mu.RLock()\n    defer c.mu.RUnlock()\n    s, ok := c.entries[key]  // never checked for expiry\n    return s, ok\n}\n```\n\n## Runbook\n\n1. Take a heap dump for analysis:\n```bash\nkubectl exec -n prod deploy/user-service -- \\\n  curl -s localhost:6060/debug/pprof/heap > heap.out\ngo tool pprof heap.out\n```\n2. If confirmed, rollback to v3.2.0:\n```bash\nkubectl rollout undo deployment/user-service -n prod\n```\n3. Monitor recovery: [JVM dashboard](https://grafana.internal/d/jvm-user-service)\n\n## References\n\n- [PR #892](https://github.com/acme/user-service/pull/892) - introduced UserSessionCache\n- [Go pprof guide](https://go.dev/blog/pprof)"
    },
